article.headline: Monmouth (N.J.) 64, Hampton 52
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Chris Kenny scored 14 points to lead Monmouth to a 64-52 victory over Hampton in the third-place game at the Paradise Jam tournament Monday night. Blake Hamilton had 13 points and nine rebounds for the Hawks (2-1). Jeff Granger had a game-high 24 points for Hampton (1-2). Devin Green finished with 14 points and 11 rebounds. Granger shot 6-for-7 from 3-point range and scored 21 points in the first half, and the Pirates (1-2) shot 8-of-14 from behind the arc. Monmouth went on a 21-0 run in the second half and the Pirates were held without a field goal for 12 minutes during the outburst. The Hawks had six of their nine steals and limited Hampton to 5-for-25 shooting from the field in the second half. Monmouth played without starting center Brian Boxler, who sustained a concussion on Sunday, and Dwayne Byfield, sidelined with an ankle injury.
